originalText.text: John is the trainer everyone needs! He is optimistic, has great energy and will always make sure to keep you accountable so you can reach your fitness goals. I saw great results when I trained with John for about 5 months! He does a combination of both strength training and cardio, which are a killer, but will get you into shape in no time. He's also super flexible with training hours, which was convenient for me, given that my schedule is constantly changing between days and nights. I would recommend John to any of my friends and family!

originalText.text: Jon is a knowledgeable and motivating trainer. He always pushes me to my limits and listens to my individual goals depending on the time of year. If you’re looking for a change or to get into a new workout routine I suggest giving him a try. He loves seeing his clients succeed and getting them into the best shape of their lives.

originalText.text: I’ve worked with a few personal trainers in my life and Jon Andrews is by far my favorite for both his skill and his personality. We were introduced after I had taken a long hiatus from the gym and needed help transitioning back and regaining my strength.. After an extensive assessment, Jon created a challenging program that was within my ability level.  I was completely out of shape and have heart palpitations which he kept in mind and monitored while he trained me. He is both patient and motivating! I’d be remiss if I didn’t say how truly awesome a person he is!! He not only helped me get stronger but is an excellent listener, and gives both great nutritional AND life advice.

originalText.text: John has been a fantastic trainer for me and I'd recommend him for anybody. I had a lot of difficulty starting to work out again after not going to the gym for years, and John helped ease me into it and gave great suggestions for being mentally and physically prepared for each workout. He really knows his expertise, not just the physical training aspect but the nutrition and recovery aspects as well.
